  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Peel and chop the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> and chopped <strong>sweet potato</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until tender and golden</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1898Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1898Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1898Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1898Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1898Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are cooking, peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>garlic </strong></p>\n<p>Strip the <strong>sage leaves</strong> from their stalks and chop them finely, discard the stalks</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1898Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1898Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1898Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1898Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1898Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>\n<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped sage</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
